Join the Conversation To find out more about Facebook commenting please read the Conversation Guidelines and FAQs Prep roundup: Sabres take 3rd at state true-team TIMES STAFF REPORT 10:54 p.m. CDT October 10, 2015 Sports brief (Photo: Times graphic) 
MINNEAPOLIS –– The Sartell Sabres finished third at the Class A state true-team girls swimming and diving championships Saturday at the University of Minnesota Aquatic Center. 
Visitation won the title with 2,147 points. Breck had 1,913 to place second. Sartell was third at 1,892. 
Melrose took sixth at 1,412 and Foley was 10th at 1,277. 
Anna Ellis finished third in the 200-yard individual medley for Sartell (2 minutes, 15.83 seconds). 
Liberty Johnson took third in the 50 freestyle (25.73) and Claire Boschee was third in diving (377.15) for the Sabres. 
Team scores –– 1. Visitaion 2,147; 2. Breck 1, 913; 3. Sartell 1,892; 4. Mankato West 1,816; 5. Northfield 1,470; 6. Melrose 1,412.5; 7. Dassel-Cokato 1,401; 8. Monticello 1,318; 9. Winona 1,301.5; 10. Foley 1,277; 11. Detroit Lakes 953; 12. Hibbing 714. 
Girls tennis 
TARROLLYS WIN 
SARTELL –– St. Cloud Tech’s Katelyn Tarrolly and Taylor Tarrolly teamed together in doubles play and won the South Sub-Section 8-2A title at Fitness Evolution. 
The victory marked the 100th career win for Katelyn Tarrolly. The sisters won 6-2, 6-0 over Becker’s Olivia Hultgren and Rachel Lukkarila, who also advance. 
Tech’s Ashley Tarrolly finished first in singles play (6-2, 6-4) and Kate Inderieden took third (6-2, 6-2) for the Tigers. 
Rebekah Zwiener and Anne Bowe finished fourth for Tech. The top four places advance to Section 8-2A competition next Saturday at Fitness Evolution. 
Brynn Sauer of Rocori and Madilyn Fesenmaier of Sartell also advanced in singles to the section tournament. Sauer finished second to Ashley Tarrolly. Fesenmaier was fourth for Sartell. 
Boys soccer 
LITTLE FALLS 5, ROCORI 2 
LITTLE FALLS –– The Flyers used four second-half goals to take down the Spartans in a nonconference match. 
Senior Cooper Berg recorded his first career hat trick to lead Little Falls (5-10-1). 
Austin Visker and Riley Loukinen also had goals for the Flyers. 
Federico Sebastian and Uriel Rodriguez each had a goal for the Spartans. 
Cross country 
SARTELL 4th AT ALEX 
ALEXANDRIA –– Alex Nemeth finished in 21st place to lead Sartell to a fourth-place finish at the Alexandria Invitational run at Arrowwood Resort. Stillwater won the invitational with 68 points. 
Lydia Anderson finished ninth to lead the Sartell girl team. 
Boys team scores –– 1. Stillwater 68; 2. Mounds View 130; 3. Willmar 140; 4. Sartell 153; 5. White Bear Lake 172; 6. Chanhassen 176; 7. Alexandria 214; 8. Marshall 256; Chaska 258. 
Girls team scores –– 1. Willmar 89; 2. Marshall 95; 3. Red Wing 103; 4. Roseville 144; 5. White Bear Lake 169; 6. Chanhassen 207; 7. Monticello 210; 8. St. Cloud Tech 235; 9. Sartell 151.
